        <section id="market" class="bg-light">
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Our Markets</h2>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8 mx-auto">
                        <p>The GPIS operates within a multi-faceted market, each with its own unique audience and set of challenges.</p>
                        <p><strong>Academic Market:</strong> Our primary market is the scientific community, specifically in the fields of epidemiology and public health. We engage with this audience through publications in high-impact journals, where our research is measured by its number and quality. We also collaborate with and present our findings to other researchers at national and international conferences. Our offering to this market is our innovative methodology and our unique focus on culturally-specific research in an LMIC setting, which differentiates us from traditional cohorts.</p>
                        <p><strong>Funding Market:</strong> We compete for grants from a variety of sources. Our national focus is on CNPq, and internationally, we target grants from organizations like Wellcome. Our value proposition to these organizations is the high-quality, impactful, and innovative research that we conduct, which aligns with their funding priorities.</p>
                        <p><strong>Community Market:</strong> Our most crucial market is the local community, including the mothers and children who participate in our studies. We engage with them through our social media presence on Instagram (@coorterg2019) and Facebook ("coorte de rg 2019"). A key challenge in this market is maintaining engagement and addressing problems with low participation rates. Our "product" for this market is the social impact of our work, including the potential for future interventions that can improve maternal and child health.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
